<A NAME="topicBasicViewUp"></A>

<H2>Change the camera view up</H2>
This function is useful when the camera is in the wrong orientation.<P>

<H2>Usage</H2>

<OL>

<LI>
<A HREF="helpMart-0051.htm">Go to the camera view</A>.

<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><img align="center" src="changeViewUp0.png"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<LI>
Press "Ctrl + V". The image will rotate 90º clock-wise each time, stop when the camera is align as you wish.

<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><img align="center" src="changeViewUp1.png"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<LI>
The correct view up will be saved.

</OL>

<H2>Shortcuts</H2>

<UL>
<LI> Ctrl + V - Rotate the image 90º clock-wise.
</UL>


